        "messages": {
          "values": [
            {
              "content": "=Write a LinkedIn post promoting my blog post. Match this style exactly:\n\n1. Start with the blog post title on its own line (no intro, no \"Hey everyone\")\n2. Write 2–4 lines that highlight what the reader will learn or gain, using relevant emojis as bullet markers (🚀 ✅ ⚠️ 💡 etc.)\n3. End with a short call-to-action line starting with 👉 followed by the link\n4. Keep it concise, punchy, and value-focused — no fluff, no hashtags\n5. Keep it within 50 -100 words\n6. Do not use `\\n` or any escape sequences. Use actual line breaks in your response.\n\nHere are examples: \n1. Let's Build A Strapi Plugin To Integrate Vercel AI SDK In Our Next.js 16 Project\n\nHere’s what you will learn:\n\n🚀 Build a Strapi plugin to centralize AI logic\n⚠️ Use Vercel AI SDK for consistent streaming + responses\n✅ Expose AI actions directly inside your CMS workflows\n\n👉 Full Tutorial: https://strapi.io/blog/let-s-build-a-strapi-plugin-to-integrate-vercel-s-ai-sdk-in-our-next-js-16-project\n\n2. Agent Skills turn repeated prompts into reusable workflows. 🚀\n\nThis guide breaks down what skills are, how they use progressive disclosure to protect context, and how to build portable skills that work across Claude, Codex, Gemini CLI, GitHub Copilot, Cursor, and more.\n\n👉 Complete guide: https://strapi.io/blog/what-are-agent-skills-and-how-to-use-them\n\n3. Automate Your Content Publishing with Strapi and n8n\n\nLearn how to automate your workflow: trigger on publish, update Airtable, create the live URL, notify Slack, and email editors when records are missing.\n\nLess manual work, fewer missed updates.\n\n👉 Full tutorial: https://strapi.io/blog/how-to-automate-your-content-workflow-with-strapi-and-n8n\n\nBlog post title: {{ $('Webhook').item.json.body.entry.title }}\nBlog post link: {{ $('Generate Entry URL').item.json.entryURL }}\nBlog post content: {{ $('Webhook').item.json.body.entry.content }}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {
          "system": "You are an experienced social media manager"
        }
      },
